              <h1>Instructions.</h1>
              <p> As a participant in this experiment, you will play a simple game consisting of a number of rounds with an agent. You are matched with an agent  across all rounds within a given game.
              </p>
	<p><span class="label label-default" role="button">Page 3</span></p>
            </div>
    </div>

    <div class="item">
      <div class="new_html_code" style='height:800px'></div>
      <div class="carousel-caption">
              <h1>This is the <u>Action Phase</u>..</h1>
              <p class="alert alert-success">Payoff Structure</p><table class='table table-bordered table-condensed'><tr><th>Option</th> <th>You will get</th> <th>The agent  will get</th> </tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choiceAction" id='first' checked='checked' value="1"> A: </td><td>-2</td><td>5</td></tr><tr><td><input type="radio" name="choiceAction" id='second' value="2"> B: </td><td>0</td><td>0</td></tr></table>

              <p >Each round of the game consists of 2 stages. In the action (first) stage, you and the agent  will be offered a choice (individually) between two options as shown above. The payoff you receive at the end of each round depends on the options that both you and the agent chose. Your payoff in each round of the experiment is thus the sum of your payoff from your chosen option and your payoff from the agent's chosen option. You choose an option by clicking the radio button labelled 'A' or 'B'. You must select your option before the timer runs out. If you do not do so, a random option will be chosen for you and you will not be paid for that round. You have 20 seconds to make a decision.</br>
              <br/>For Example, if you choose A and your opponent chooses A, you will get -2 + 5 = 3.
              <br/> The timer below will be counting down in real play.
    <div class="alert alert-info">10 seconds remaining...</div>
          <br/>
              <p><span class="label label-default" role="button">Page 4</span></p>
            </div>
    </div>

    <div class="item">
      <div class="new_html_code" style='height:600px'></div>
      <div class="carousel-caption">
              <h1>Review Phase</h1>
              <table class='table table-bordered'><tr><td></td><td></td><td> You got</td></tr>
<tr><td>Your Choice : </td><td>A <span class="badge  pull-right">R</span></td><td> -2 </td></tr>"
    <tr><td>Opponent Choice : </td><td>B</td><td>0</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Total</td><td></td><td>-2</td></tr></table>
              <p>In the review (second) stage, both you and the agent are presented with the options chosen in the previous stage. You are also shown the payoff you received from your chosen action, the payoff you received from the agent's chosen option and your resulting total score. The cumulative total score at the end of all rounds is multiplied by $0.01 to give your total bonus. You will be given 10 seconds to reflect on the result after which a new round starts automatically. The <span class="badge">R</span>  indicates that the you did not choose anything within the time frame</p>
                 <p><span class="label label-default" role="button">Page 5</span></p>
            </div>
    </div>

    <div class="item">
      <div class="new_html_code" style='height:600px'></div>
      <div class="carousel-caption">
              <h1>Comprehension Questions</h1>
              <p> You will now answer 2 short questions to show that you understood the instructions and how to play the game. After answering successfully, you will be placed in a waiting room where you will wait until you are assigned another participant to play the game with. The game will start as soon as a partner has joined the game, at which point a beep will alert you. Once a game has started, leaving the game before the final summary screen will result in you not getting paid AT ALL.
              </p>Please note the two circumstances which could make you forfeit your entire payment:</p>
              <ul>
              <li>Once in the waiting room, you leave the waiting room before the waiting room timer runs out.</li>
              <li>Once in a game, you stop or close a game at any time before the final payment screen.</li></p>
